2228.name: Goods exports (BoP, current US$)
2228.description: Goods exports refer to all movable goods (including nonmonetary gold and net exports of goods under merchanting) involved in a change of ownership from residents to nonresidents. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
2228.datasetName: World Development Indicators - Economic Policy & Debt
2228.s_name: World Bank - WDI: Goods exports (BoP, current US$)

source.name: World Bank - WDI: Goods exports (BoP, current US$)
source.dataPublisherSource: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
source.additionalInfo: General comments: Note: Data are based on the sixth edition of the IMF's Balance of Payments Manual (BPM6) and are only available from 2005 onwards. Merchanting is reclassified from services to goods.

2334.name: Service exports (BoP, current US$)
2334.description: Services refer to economic output of intangible commodities that may be produced, transferred, and consumed at the same time. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
2334.datasetName: World Development Indicators - Economic Policy & Debt
2334.s_name: World Bank - WDI: Service exports (BoP, current US$)

source.name: World Bank - WDI: Service exports (BoP, current US$)
source.dataPublisherSource: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
source.additionalInfo: General comments: Note: Data are based on the sixth edition of the IMF's Balance of Payments Manual (BPM6) and are only available from 2005 onwards. Manufacturing services on physical inputs owned by others (goods for processing in BPM5) and maintenance and repair services n.i.e. are reclassified from goods to services.
